 Each vertex's state is drawn from a finite set of possible states with some probability of observance.
 Vertex probabilities represent the complete set of possibilities for the vertex and are mutually exclusive.
 The conditional probability tables (CPTs) of each vertex are used to calculate the joint probability of a proposition using Bayes Theorem.
 CPTs can be filled from experiments by the practitioner that mimic case circumstances;
 published probabilities similar to the case;
 a range of reasonable values;
 or based on the practitioners prior experience or knowledge 
