\begin_layout Standard
BNs show an interesting characteristic that the state of a vertex is conditional only on the state of its parents and not the state of any other vertex in the network,
 a characteristic known as conditional independence.
 This characteristic enables a reduction in the number of factors that need to be incorporated into the joint probability calculation for scenarios.
 As computation power availability grows,
 more complex BNs can be developed.
\end_layout

